This type of arrangement is a great way to showcase both candles and flowers in water. If you use fresh flowers for this arrangement, assemble them on one day before the wedding or the day of the wedding to ensure the flowers stay fresh.Use any container of your choice. If you are only using one container, look for one that is wide and short so it can fit a few candles and flowers. If you are using several containers, try using ones at different heights or widths. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/8f/Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-17Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-17Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/8/8f/Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-17Bullet1.jpg/aid1395302-v4-728px-Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-17Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Fill the container or containers up with water. Leave an inch or two of space. If you’d like to add in more color, add a few drops of food coloring to the water. Add the food coloring prior to pouring the water in the containers so the colors do not leave dye marks on the flowers. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/01/Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-17Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-17Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/0/01/Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-17Bullet2.jpg/aid1395302-v4-728px-Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-17Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Cut the stems off of the flowers. You really want to showcase the buds of the flowers so remove the stems so there is only about an inch of stem under the buds. Flowers with shapely buds like orchids, roses, and lilies are great options. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/e6/Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-17Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-17Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/e/e6/Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-17Bullet3.jpg/aid1395302-v4-728px-Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-17Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Alternatively, you can glue the stems onto the bottom of the container with a glue gun to keep them in place. If you decide to use this method, glue the flowers down before you fill the container with water. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/04/Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-17Bullet4.jpg/v4-460px-Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-17Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/0/04/Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-17Bullet4.jpg/aid1395302-v4-728px-Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-17Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Place the floating candles on the surface of the water, around the flowers. Floating candles are specially made for use near or in water and can burn for several hours to ensure you have beautiful centerpieces throughout the entire reception. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/c2/Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-17Bullet5.jpg/v4-460px-Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-17Bullet5.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/c/c2/Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-17Bullet5.jpg/aid1395302-v4-728px-Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-17Bullet5.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

From 50’s flapper glamour to refined English countryside, focusing on a certain style of time period can be a creative way to come up with the perfect centerpiece. Some ideas for a period inspired center piece might be:Hollywood Heyday: Think old Hollywood glamor, with dashes of fur to compliment the champagne and sparkles on the tables and luxe colors like gold and silver on the centerpieces. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/2e/Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-18Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-18Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/2/2e/Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-18Bullet1.jpg/aid1395302-v4-728px-Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-18Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Renaissance Revival: Decorate the tables with rich tapestries and luxurious silks, as well as bright flowers and fabrics on the centerpieces. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/3f/Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-18Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-18Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/3/3f/Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-18Bullet2.jpg/aid1395302-v4-728px-Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-18Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Victorian invasion: Go regal and set a scene Queen Elizabeth I would feel right at home in, with heirloom silverware, dainty fine china, and vivid floral centerpieces that really personify a classic English garden. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/56/Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-18Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-18Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/5/56/Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-18Bullet3.jpg/aid1395302-v4-728px-Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-18Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Vintage: Indulge in the kitsch and deck out the wedding tables with old wooden Coca-Cola boxes, mason jars, or vintage stemware. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/17/Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-18Bullet4.jpg/v4-460px-Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-18Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/1/17/Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-18Bullet4.jpg/aid1395302-v4-728px-Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-18Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Really commit to the theme by being very detail oriented in every facet of the centerpiece. Some ideas include:

The Great Gatsby: Create centerpieces with whimsical gold spirals and long white feathers or use the book’s famous blue and yellow cover as a color palette for the floral arrangements. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/8\/82\/Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-19Bullet1.jpg\/v4-460px-Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-19Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"\/images\/thumb\/8\/82\/Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-19Bullet1.jpg\/aid1395302-v4-728px-Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-19Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}


Harry Potter: Gather your magic wands, create labels for each of the houses of Hogwarts, and pepper the centerpieces with white owls. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/d\/dc\/Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-19Bullet2.jpg\/v4-460px-Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-19Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"\/images\/thumb\/d\/dc\/Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-19Bullet2.jpg\/aid1395302-v4-728px-Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-19Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

The Wizard of Oz: Break out the monkey statues, wicker baskets, and accents of shiny red (a throwback to Dorothy’s famed ruby slippers). And don’t forget to add emerald green florals to represent the city of Oz. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/3\/3f\/Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-19Bullet3.jpg\/v4-460px-Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-19Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"\/images\/thumb\/3\/3f\/Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-19Bullet3.jpg\/aid1395302-v4-728px-Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-19Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}


Game of Thrones: If you’re a fan of the fantasy epic and want to bring a bit of the TV show’s intrigue, glamor, and magic into your special day, create centerpieces based on the colors or animal symbols for the five noble houses in the realm, roaring dragons included, as well as darker reds and purples for the floral accents. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/9\/98\/Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-19Bullet4.jpg\/v4-460px-Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-19Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"\/images\/thumb\/9\/98\/Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-19Bullet4.jpg\/aid1395302-v4-728px-Make-Wedding-Centerpieces-Step-19Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}
